Overview:  <a href=" http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finder_%28comics%29" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finder_%28comics%29</a>   (beware spoilers)

Contains:   Sin-Eater                   (1996, 2011) (Digital-1024)     (Empire)
            Mystery Date                (1999, 2011) (Digital-1024)     (Empire)
            King of the Cats            (1999, 2011) (Digital-1024)     (Empire)
            Talisman                    (2000, 2011) (Digital-1024)     (Empire)
            Dream Sequence              (2001, 2011) (Digital-1024)     (Empire)
            The Rescuers                (2003, 2011) (Digital-1024)     (Empire)
            Five Crazy Women            (2005, 2011) (Digital-1024)     (Empire)
            Voice                       (2006, 2011) (Digital-1280) (G85-Empire)
            Third World      (from DHP) (2011)       (Digital-1280)     (Empire)

Compiled mainly from the recent Digital Lo-Res re-release of the 2-volume omnibus (cf <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/11240577" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/11240577</a>  ) and 2012 releases of "Voice" and "Dark Horse Presents" 1 thru 21 (for "Third World"). Each volume is bookended with its trade edition covers, includes a full cover gallery, and is accompanied by separate author's notes (except "Third World"). This revision puts them in original publication order, which IMO invariably offers a more rewarding reading experience
